    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1903</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of the Navy</hi>:</p>
                <p>Your telegram of the 9th of November to the <hi rend="italic">Boston</hi>
                    acknowledged. No interference British vessels yet. Report seems to be well
                    founded that the steamship <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi> sailed from
                    Buenaventura yesterday afternoon with 1,000 for Rio Dulce. Have sent <hi
                        rend="italic">Concord</hi> to patrol in that vicinity in order to prevent
                    landing. Everything is quiet at Panama.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Glass.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
